#: 21337012-0-1231
msgctxt "21337012-0-1231"
msgid ""
"I'll say this about the Orcs: I'm sure glad they're on our side now.\n"
"\n"
"It wasn't always like that. Forty years ago, my grandfather fought in a raid "
"on Orsinium. Those Orcs are relentless, he said. When an Orc's bleeding, and "
"you've broken one of his bones, and he's getting back on his feet after "
"you've knocked him down in the mud, that's the worst, because that's when "
"he's even more dangerous. \n"
"\n"
"That's why we worked with the Redguards to raze Orsinium to the ground. "
"That's why we burned down every Orc stronghold we could find and stamped on "
"the ashes—because we knew the Orcs would get back up again. We knew the best "
"we could do was just delay them.\n"
"\n"
"Nowadays Orsinium is stronger than ever—but we all know that we've got worse "
"problems than Orcs.\n"
"\n"
"I would expect the Orcs to hold a grudge about us keeping them down, but "
"that's one of the strange things about dealing with an Orc. I've actually "
"seen one punch another in the face. The guy who got a broken nose just stood "
"there and grinned. They might fight, or one of them might die, but Orcs make "
"sure that whatever's going on, it's going to get settled real quick. And "
"then it's over.\n"
"\n"
"When we burned down Orsinium, it was a bit more than a punch in the face, "
"but the Orcs made sure a treaty settled all that real quick.\n"
"\n"
"I've never met an Orc who wasn't good in a fight, but I get the feeling some "
"of them really want more to their lives than fighting. I guess when you live "
"or die by the swords and armor you've made, you learn to make them right the "
"first time. I'm still stunned by how good their craftsmanship is. "
"Everything's built to last.\n"
"\n"
"I think both of us—the Bretons and the Orcs—realized we could make a lot "
"more money trading with each other than fighting with each other. And if "
"there's one thing Bretons know how to do, it's make money. Well, it's not "
"the only thing we do, but you get the idea.\n"
"\n"
"I know where I stand with an Orc. I also know where I stand with the Nords: "
"and if they think they can still send raiding parties into High Rock, well, "
"now we've got an army of Orcs on our side ready to kick their arses all the "
"way back to Skyrim.\n"
"\n"
"And that's why I always say: I'm sure glad those Orcs are on our side."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1231
msgctxt "51188213-0-1231"
msgid "Orcs? Could Be Worse"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1180
msgctxt "21337012-0-1180"
msgid ""
"Brazzefk was once a Dwemer alchemist of great renown. Legend holds that his "
"search for immortality culminated in a potion designed to turn him into a "
"living giant of stone, free from the failings of flesh. The potion worked "
"all too well, turning his entire body into a stuatue, immortal but immobile.\n"
"\n"
"Is this the head of Brazzefk? And is he aware of his surroundings? We can "
"but speculate."
msgstr ""

